-- Wetston Named to Head Ontario Securities Commission, Replacing Wilson
-- B y   D o u g   A l e x a n d e r
-- 2010-10-13T15:14:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-13/wetston-named-to-head-ontario-securities-commission-replacing-wilson.html
Ontario Energy Board Chief Executive
Officer  Howard Wetston  was appointed chairman and CEO of the
Ontario Securities Commission, Canadaâ€™s largest provincial
securities regulator.  Ontario Finance Minister  Dwight Duncan  named Wetston to
succeed  David Wilson , 65, whose five-year term ends Oct. 31,
according to a  statement  today from the Ontario government. The
appointment is subject to review by the Standing Committee on
Government Agencies.  Wetston, a former vice chairman of the Ontario Securities
Commission, has been chairman and CEO of the Ontario Energy
Board since 2003. Before then, he was a judge at the Federal
Court of Canada.  The federal government plans to create a national
securities regulator by 2012 to combine the provincial agencies
that oversee capital markets in the country.  To contact the reporter on this story:
